org.modelio.metamodel.bpmn.gateways

Interface BpmnExclusiveGateway

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BpmnBaseElement, BpmnFlowElement, BpmnFlowNode, BpmnGateway, java.lang.Comparable<MObject>, Element, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, MObject, ModelElement, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier

    public interface BpmnExclusiveGateway
extends BpmnGateway
    BpmnExclusiveGateway v0.0.9054 A diverging Exclusive Gateway (Decision) is used to create alternative paths within a Process flow. This is basically the ?diversion point in the road? for a Process. For a given instance of the Process, only one of the paths can be taken. A Decision can be thought of as a question that is asked at a particular point in the Process. The question has a defined set of alternative answers. Each question is associated with a condition Expression that is associated with a Gateway?s outgoing Sequence Flow.
